HEADWORD: Xiphius
<hw>Xiph"i*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>xi`fos</grk> a sword.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
cetaceans having a long, pointed, bony beak, usually two tusklike teeth
in the lower jaw, but no teeth in the upper jaw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

